{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow all parents of dependent children to access Bereavement Support Payment",
        "additional_details": "Children in bereaved families should be supported, regardless of their parent's relationship.\r\n \r\nMy children\u2019s lives suddenly changed forever, when aged 7 and 9, their father passed away. We don\u2019t meet the BSP eligibility criteria, because we were divorced & not cohabitating at the time of death. We believe this is unjust and should be changed.\r\n \r\nOn top of supporting my children through their grief, I have the financial worry of supporting them alone. Children are entitled to receive maintenance from a non-resident parent and shouldn\u2019t be excluded from financial support when a parent dies.\r\n",
        "background": "To ensure all dependent children who have lost a parent can benefit from this support, by extending this payment to non-cohabiting parents of dependent children, even if they were not married or in a civil partnership with the deceased.",
